Date: 7/5/2008
Source: Internet - see Notes
Author:
Vol / Page: 1
Edition:
Quote: The Save Manapouri campaign has been lauded as "the birth of the modern conservation movement" in New Zealand. The Save Manapouri campaign began in the late 1950s with the proposal to build a power station to supply power to an aluminium smelter in the far south of New Zealand and gained momentum in the 1960s when it was proposed that the level of Lake Manapouri would be raised 8.2 metres to harness its hydro-electric potential for the project.
Notes: www.forestandbird.org.nz/what-we-do/publications/forest-bird-magazine/article

